with-cama','','','2009-09-29 03:28:53','2009-09-29 01:28:53','',10,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=18',0,'page','',0),(19,1,'2009-09-29 03:28:18','2009-09-29 01:28:18','Job','Get involved with CAMA','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision','','','2009-09-29 03:28:18','2009-09-29 01:28:18','',18,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=19',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2009-10-10 11:14:36','2009-10-10 09:14:36','','Where and how we work','','inherit','open','open','','26-revision','','','2009-10-10 11:14:36','2009-10-10 09:14:36','',26,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=27',0,'revision','',0),(28,1,'2009-10-10 11:15:38','2009-10-10 09:15:38','Key Achievements\r\n1997 - CAMA took MHC to court for raising rentals by 130% and was instead raised by 26%\r\n\r\n1997 - CAMA carried out study on distribution and pricing of sugar. This exposed sugar barons and a cartel, that made sugar prices become unfordable and unaccessible to most of the poor in Malawi. After the report, the owners(SUCOMA) changed distribution and pricing systems.\r\n\r\n1998 - Lobbied for the enactment of a competition and fair trading act.\r\n\r\n2000 - Aspects of consumer rights into the school curriculum; Social Studies\r\n\r\n2003 - Lobbied for the enactment of a comprehensive consumer protection law.','Key achievements','','publish','closed','closed','','key-achievements','','','2009-10-13 03:32:53','2009-10-13 01:32:53','',12,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=28',0,'page','',0),(29,1,'2009-10-10 11:15:22','2009-10-10 09:15:22','','Key achievements','','inherit','open','open','','28-revision','','','2009-10-10 11:15:22','2009-10-10 09:15:22','',28,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=29',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2009-10-10 11:16:14','2009-10-10 09:16:14','','Contact us','','publish','closed','closed','','contact-us','','','2009-10-10 11:17:43','2009-10-10 09:17:43','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=30',5,'page','',0),(31,1,'2009-10-10 11:16:02','2009-10-10 09:16:02','','Contact us','','inherit','open','